metadata.name: Generative Fantasies: 101 Compositions #48
metadata.description:
This could be a follow-up to Herbert W. Franke's finding of interesting connections between Constructivism and Generative art, where at first, technological limits allowed only simple line drawings, based on fixed proportions, and later were extended by the use of random generators. Constructivism, as an art movement, sought to depict modern civilization, the symbiotic relationship between technology and art, industrialization, and urban spaces. Iakov Chernikhov (Яков Чернихов), an architect and graphic artist, was one of the influential figures in Constructivism. He extensively used the two-point perspective with an observation point below the ground in his drawings. 

In this (my) exploration of two-point perspective, random, colorful, and glassy constructions visual resemblance to Chernikhov’s oeuvre is inescapable. Therefore the title is a play on the original title of his book Architectural Fantasies: 101 Compositions in Color, 101 Architectural Miniatures from 1933.

The subtle grain effect is done with p5.grain library by Gorilla Sun (@gorillasu) & meezwhite (@meezwhite). 

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations.

metadata.name: gate home #29
metadata.description:
house. everyone should have their own home. this is as important as air or water. you can live without a home, but is this the life you want? you can travel, live for years in different countries, but in the end you will return to your home where you will get comfort and peace. that's what I found in this artwork.
the lines neatly bypass all the chaos of the center, like a man in his house. they seem to hide from all danger and create their own order.

metadata.name: Dragons #45
metadata.description:
A grid of many lines forming a dragon crafted on paper.
They all have their own personality... Be sure to name and take care of them.

tw: williamapan

metadata.name: Leviathan #14
metadata.description:
Leviathan is a generative collection of large bodies made form particles, materialised from the viewers own subconscious. Atoms form gargantuan objects - subatomic monoliths and microscopic giants. Playing with the sense of scale it draws on the viewer’s subjective way of associating forms, a pattern that becomes a mirror, a skeleton for them to project. 

Part artist, part viewer. Leviathan asks us to question these relationships of creation, ownership and meaning. It is a chemical reaction that the artist starts and you finish. A colossal dream we are all sharing together - a leviathan.


Controls:
s or double tap: Download image
1 : Download 2400 x 4000
2 : Download 3600 x 6000
3 : Download 4800 x 8000
4 : Download 7200 x 12000

metadata.name: Separation in the Night #103
metadata.description:
For this project I was strongly inspired by the paintings of Mark Rothko, Jackson Pollock, Kazemir Malevich, but mostly token refers to the works of one of the largest figures of the European avant-garde, Paul Klee. I wanted to convey that complex color mood and atmosphere that artist achieved with oil paints. 
I have been working with color palettes and functions for a long time to make complex transitions and gradients. This code has really huge potential for a wide diversity of artworks and I would like to see as many interesting variations as possible. Enjoy<3

Project contains:

•three canvas types : horizontal, vertical, square
•rare features : vertical stripes, posterization
•press "p" to pause animation and play again
•open in tab and press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #4620
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #103
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Ephemera #77
metadata.description:
Reflecting on fleeting things. A study of light, wildflowers, and wind.

This project is best viewed using Chrome on a computer with a modern GPU.

A special thanks to the creators of p5.js and color.js whose excellent tools helped make this project possible.

metadata.name: September #227
metadata.description:
The Summer Ends
---------------
Controls:
S or double tap (mobile): Download image

A: Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)

1-6: Modify scale (1 = default, 1500 x 2000px, 6 = maximum, 9000 x 12000px (performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F: Fit to current screen size

T: Toggle grain and texture overlay
H: Toggle shape outlines

B: Cycle border sizes (0 -> 50 -> 75 -> 100 -> 150px)
C: Cycle border colors

I: Cycle visible layers

L: Toggle “live mode”. This mode will continuously redraw a new output every few seconds using the same base parameters as the original output, but with slight variations.

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------
teaboswell 2022

10% of primary sales will be donated to Girls Who Code (https://girlswhocode.com)

metadata.name: Primordial #99
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022
